Only type of relationships you need to understand in your life to avoid oops mistakes…
enough of catch line now focus on work, In object oriented programming (oops) we usually find three relationships are Association(uses a) , Aggregation(weak has ) and composition(strong has).
In term of relationship strength:
Association(I know about it) < Aggregation(I have it) < composition(I own it) you can use it to learn them. What can be trick to recall the in interview is “know association ,have aggregation and own composition”.
First , target Association (I know about it):
In association , our class can use object of each other without taking the responsibilities of each other object , I will explain in simple with example.
class Student {
String name; Student(String name) {
this.name = name;
}
}
class Teacher {
String name;
Teacher(String name) {
this.name = name;
}
void teach(Student student) {
System.out.println(name + " teaches " + student.name);
}
}
public class AssociationExample {
public static void main(String[] args) {
Student student = new Student("John");
Teacher teacher = new Teacher("Smith");
teacher.teach(student);
}
}
In above example , Teacher class is using the object of Student do it’s work and leave don’t care about where it’s being created, what it’s origin only thing is that Teacher class know about it. Ohk , but how Teacher class know about Student object observe in above example we are passing Student object inside the method of Teacher class and there we used it (know about it) then, our job is complete Teacher class forget about it.
This is the weakest type of relation ship .
Second, target is Aggregation (I have it):
In aggregation ,our class can use the object without creating it and without knowing the origin of it. I will explain with example
class Professor {
String name; Professor(String name) {
this.name = name;
}
}
class Department {
String name;
Professor professor;
Department(String name, Professor professor) {
this.name = name;
this.professor = professor;
}
void display() {
System.out.println(
professor.name + " works in " + name + " department."
);
}
}
public class AggregationExample {
public static void main(String[] args) {
Professor professor = new Professor("Alice");
Department dept = new Department("Computer Science", professor);
dept.display();
}
}
In above example , read it carefully this is tricky OK , observe that in Department class using the object of Professor class as the parameter for the constructor in Department class and inside Department class we have Professor professor instance variable(variable inside the class) which in future become the variable inside the object(instance) too.Now, we are initialising the instance variable of type Professor which named as professor inside the constructor of Department class mind the word initialisation not creation ok that means Department class does not know the origin of Professor object (here it’s begin created inside the Aggregation class but Department class does not care about) but it’s being injected the constructor of Department class and initialising it’s instance variable of type Professor that it.So, in short Department class have instance variable of type Professor it’s does not own it(like create inside it) eg.Professor professor=new Professor(); inside it’s constructor
Third, Composition(I own it):
In composition , our class create the object of other class inside it constructor and this time it’s know it’s origin which is it’s own constructor and while taking it’s full responsiblity(like if my object deads you will dead along me as your being created inside by constructor lol). I will explain with example.
class Room {
Room() {
System.out.println("Room created");
}
}class House {
private Room room;
House() {
room = new Room(); // created inside House
}
void show() {
System.out.println("House has a room");
}
}
public class CompositionExample {
public static void main(String[] args) {
House house = new House();
house.show();
}
}
In above example , simply observed that House class constructor is actually creating the object of Room class inside it’s constructor which implies it’s know’s it’s origin , it’s ready to take it’s full responsibility(if my object dead you are going to dead with him) which introduced to concept of object lifecycle. In short , lifecycle simply meaning the amount the object will stay in memory of program ok for example Department and Professor from aggregation, Professor class Object(child object we are going to use) can exist without parent object(who is going to use child object ) ie.Department class. But in above example , Room object(child object remember it’s not inheritance don’t confuse with it ok it child object not child class I am using this for you understanding only ok ) can not exist without parent object(House) what it’s there origin this time CompositionExample class if we don’t create House object we will never create a Room Object ok .
